{"/service/ndnp/kyu/batch_kyu_joplin_ver01/data/sn86069395/00175045545/1910082301/0850.xml":{"full_text":"1J fiY lclIYIi wK\nI i4 Bill LOT SALE ON TUESDAY Aft 30TU 1910\nt J\nj 1 I 30BEAUTIFUL LETS30\nL w\n1\ntji ff to\niT IN CHOICE RESIDENCE SECTION OF THE CITY\nIn the Davis and Oldham addition on West 15th Street These lots are located on good elevation and in\n4ii good residence part of the city They are now being graded This will be a rare opportunity for a good\ninvestment or a pretty home site close In town West 17th and West 18th streets have been extended\nAuctioneersk5\nk5 VALUABLE PRESENTS TO BE GIVEN AWAY\nJt DAVIS OLDHAM\nI\nJL i r Mi1WoiIuhFbloA\nf\ni r\ni\nCRACK SHOT\nPo\nI\niGov Willsons Private Sec\nii retary Beats Them All\nli\nLondon Ky Aug 20 Capt\nI Jackson Morris of Frankfort pri\ntvate secretary to Gov Willson who\nmade the highest score of all those\nwho competed for place on the 1\nKentucky team to the national shoot\ning tournament at Camp Peary 0\nis probably the best allround shot\np in Kentucky He and eleven other\nft Kentuckians are at Camp Peary at\ntending the tournament He has II\nr won scores of medals in some of the\nmost important matches in the\nf country\nf\nCapt Morris was born in Breath\nf 1 ytt county where he was reared\ne has held many important posi\ntions He was assistant secretary of\nstate until recentlywhen he resigned\nn to take the appointment as secreta\n1 ry to the Governor Hunting fish\nr ing and target shooting are his hob\njjjl bies He is well known and very\nt popular\nf\nI THE RACE IN NEBRASKA\ni f Indications Are That Dahl I\nk mans Majority is 1000\n5\ntS rPniaha Neb Aug 20Although\nH Guv Shallenberger has not as yet\nyeti\nit cratic nomination for the head df\nthe State ticket a telegram was re\nf ceiyed here from one of his cam\niLpaign managers Chris Grunther\nl vice chairman of the Democratic\ni State commitjteegiving up the fight\nf i Mayor Dahlmans majority has been\nf\nt Considerably reduced from first esti\nmates but will apparently be not\nf far from 1000 votes\ntff Complete returns from fiftyone\ncounties give Congressman Hitch\nl s cock for United States Senator on\nJ the Democratic ticket a twotoone\nif majority over both his opponents\nI and more than three times the vote\nof his nearest competitor Richard\n7 L Metcalfe\nt Late returns from the Republican\nl primaries only increase the lead of\nAldrich over Cady for Governor\nWith but 300 precincts to hear from\nf Aldrichs lead is more than 3000\nCOUNTY TAXES\n5 Pay your State and County Taxes\nr now and avoid the rush Two reo\nt1r ceipts to write\nLOW JOHNSON\nSheriff Christian Co\nWall Streets Discontent\nv\nWall Street estimates that ap\nK proximately 1500000000 will be\nspent this year by Americans for the\npurchase of automobiles Qf this\nvast sum probably 85 per cent will\nbe for machines of domestic make\nthe only foreign product in which\nwill be rubber for the tires of which\nabout 75000000 will be used\nIt computed by statisticians of\nG New Yorks financial district that\nr half of this outlay would be used for\nstock market speculation but for the\nnation wide craze for joy cars\nr With such an enormous amount of\nF money diverted from stock trading\nchannels conditions in The Street are\nnow akin to those that prevailed\nduring the 1907 panic In six months\nthere has been a shrinkage of 150\n000900 in the market value securl\nties dealt in upon the stock exchange\ndue mainly to the lack of public\nsupport The lambs always a fruit\nful source of revenue for the wily\nbulls and bears no longer gambol\nwith their old abandon and have be\ncome as scarce as hens teeth about\nWall Nassau and Broad streets All\nthat are left are the professional\ntraders to whom the limited pickings\nare not over attractive\nIn the hope of checking the spread\nof the automobile tide the assistance\nI of local bankers has been enlisted\nThe latter are now vociferously dep\nrecating the mania They claim it\nis inrioculating the small business\nI men of the country as well as the\naffluent merchants of the city and\nthat in order to gratify their appe\ntite for machines this class is mort\ngaging its homes and property This\ncry of alarm however is not borne\nout by the mortgage records which\nshow but a normal state of borrow\ning on real estate Neither do the\nreports of the clearing house indi\ncate that bank deposits are being\nge\nappreciably withdrawn to enable\ncustomers to biy machines What\ntc\nmoney is being used by the public\nfor the pu chase of cars is its sur\nfouni\nplus cash which in other years found\nits way into stock exchange houses\nfor less exhilarating employment\nThis is the money that created in\nflated and fictitious markets and\nenabled the gamblers of the street\nto live in opulence while their clients\ngrew two gray hairs where there\nwas one before\nThroughout the financial district\nespecially among those who depend\nupon the outside public for their\nbusiness there seem to be a disposi\ntion to deplore the recent purchase\nbyJ Piefepont Morgan of the con\ntrolling interest in one of the largest\nof the domestic automobile factories\nThey think it will have a bad effect\non the market and help to retard\nthe return of prosperity in The\nStreet by giving undue prestige to\nthe industry to whose development\nthey attribute most of their trou\nbles Their chagrin recalls the feel\ning existing in the district some\nyears ago daring one of the inter\nmittent periods of depression to\nwhich it is subject when John D\nRockefellow instead of supporting n\ndeclinirg market dumped several of\nhis millions ihto the stock of the\nquick lunch restaurants of the big\neastern cities which have since net\nted him handsome profits\nIn reply to Wall Streets lament\nanent the diversion of money from\nthe stock market the president of\none of the large automobile com\npanies this week threw a jolt into\nthe enemys camp in a statement\nsaying that the public had grown\ntired of frittering away its savings\nin Wall Street gambling that rarely\nnetted it anything but headaches\nand insomnia and had determined\nto get some wholesale pleasure out\ntf\nof its cash through the purchase of\nmachines that would enable them to\ngive enjoyment and recreation to\nothers as well as to themselves\nStill Down on George III\nA movement looking to the replac\ning of the statue of King George III\nin New York has met with vigorous\nopposition by members of the\nDaughters of the American Revolu\ntion\nFOR SALEThe life of Edward\nAlonzo Pennington 25c C B Brew\ner Elkton RF P 2\ne\nI I\nj\nJ\nKENTUCKY PHYSICIAN\nHas Claim on 25000 Prop\nerty In Germany\nLouisville Ky August 21Dr\nErnest Moraweck formerly a wel\nknown physician of Louisville has\nfallen heir to a villa in Germany\nI worth 25000 under circumstance\nao unosual that he is meeting some\nI delay in getting possession of the\nproperty Dr Moraweck was in\nEurope last year and while return\ning on the steamer in the fall he be\ncame acquainted with Mrs Raas a\nwealthy German widow who was\nsr\ncoming to America to visit her\nbrother and travel through the\ncountry MrsRaaswho was an elder\nly woman was so pleased with Dr\nMoraweck that when she took a trip\nthrough the country he went as her\ncompanion and on their return\nstopped at Dr Morawecks place in\nMeade county Ky There Mrs\nRaas died in April of heart trouble\nand complications Dr Moraweck\nproduced A codicil to the will the\noriginal being in Germany This\ni codicil left Dr Moraweck her villa\nin Germany and directed that her\nbody be cremated and the ashes to\nken back to Germany and placed be\nside the body of her husband The\nremains were cremated and Dr\nMoraweck took the ashes to Germany\nand offered the codicil The heirs\nin Germany object to it and an in\nternational legal battle is promised\n12YEAROLD HEROINE\nHEROINEMan\nSaves Life of Drowning Man\nand Receives Medal\nCulver Ind Aug 19By saving\nthe life of F Thompson of Atlanta\nGa while both were swimming in\nLake Maxinkukee today twelve\nyear old Isabelle Fuller daughter of\nE R Fuller of Richmond Va be\ncame the heroine of the cottagers of\nthe summer resort\nThompson is an expert swimmer\nbut was seized with cramps when he\nwas 300 feet from a pier The little\ngirl also an adept was swimming\nnear him When she saw he was\nsinking she quickly swam to him and\nsupported him until a boating party\ncame to their rescue\nIn the presence of hundreds of vis\nitors and the entire cadet corps of\nthe Culver summer naval school\ndrawn up on the campus this after\nnoon Miss Fuller WES presented\nwith a gold medal by the academy\nthrough the commandant as a rec\nognition of her courage\ni IT r MPTPi fcT\nKEGENSTEIN\nMakes Public School Bock\nList Selected by Franklin\nCounty\nSuperintendent of Public Instruc\ntion Regenstein has made public the\nHat of books that have been selected\nby the Franklin County High School\nText Book Commission that will bo\nUsed in the high schools of this coup\nty during the next tour years The\nbooks exchange prices and net\ncontract price and rho successful\nbidders follow\nAMERICAN BOOK CO CINCINNATI 0\nHarkness Complete Latin Grand\nmar exchange price 75 cents net\ncontract price 92 cents\nPearsons Essentials of Latin ex\nchange price 54 cents net contract\nprice 67 cents\nHarkness Forbes Caesars Com\nmentaries on the Gallic War Four\nI Books exchange price GO cents net\ns contract price 75 cents\nHarper Millers Virgils Aeneid\ns exchange price 75 cents net contract\ne price 93 cents\nPearsons Latin Prose Composition\n1 Based on Caesar exchange price 30\ncents net contract price 37 cents\nPearons Latin Prose Composition\nI Based on Cicero exchange price 30\ncents net contract price 37 cents\nMatthews Introduction to Ameri\ncan Literature exchange price 60\ncents net contract price 75 cents\nGINN COMPANY CHICAGO ILL\nWentworths Elementary Algebra\nexchange price 67 cents net contract\ncontractfPrice\nI Wentworths Plane and Solid\nI Geometry Revised exchange price\ni70 cents net contract price 100\nL Wentworths Advanced Arithme\ntic exchange price 60 cents net con\nI tract price 80 cents\nDavis Elementary Physical\nGeography exchange price 75 cents\nnet contract price 100\nMillikan Gales First Course in\nPhysics exchange price 75 cents net i\ncontract price 100\nMyers General History Revised\nexchange price 75 cents net con\ntract price 120\nWentworths Plane Trigonometry\nand Tables exchange price 54 cents\nnet contract price 72 cents\nHENRY HOLT CO NEW YORK CITY\nPancoasts Introduction to Eng\nlish Literature exchange price 81\ncents net contract price 101\nPracticeg\nBook in English Composition ex\nchange price 60 cents net contract\nprice 75 cents\nCotswold Sheep For Sale\nFour yearling bucks weighing\nfrom 220 to 240 lbs These bucks\nsheared from 22 to 25 Ibs wool in\nthespring Have been dipped reg\nularly and are healthy Also several\nbuck lambs weighing over 100 Ibs\nGARNETTd\nJURY IN BROWNE CASE\nOn Huudred Agents at Work\n\nFor Defense\nChicago Aug 19A jury to try\nLee ONeil Browne Democratic\nleader of the lower house at Spring\nfield Ill for the second time on a\ncharge of bribery of Representative\nWhite to vote for William Lorimer\nfor United States Senator was\nsworn in today by Judge Kuraten in\nthe criminal court\nStates Attorney Wayman admitted\ntoday that he had identified two of\nthe alleged investigators who he de\nclares are working for the defense\nin the Lee ONeil Browne case\nTheir names are Adolph Cheffer and\nFrettL Backer It is charged that\nthey are operators of a private\ndetective agency which has 100 men\nat work for Browne Counsel for\nthe defense state that none of their\ninvestigators has been asked to see\nthe families of veniremenI\nI\nSee J H Dagg for contracting II\nbuilding and general repair work of I\nall kinds Phone 478 I\nI mum I\nEIGHT CHAPTERS\nIn TheDemocratic Text Book\nWhich Arrives in Chicago\nChicago Aug 21Callers at the\noffice of Roger C Sullivan Demo\ncratic National Committeeman for\nIllinois today were shown the first\ncopy of the Democratic National\ntextbook that has been seen in these\npartsIt\nIt is divided into eight chapters\nand the titles of these give a fairly\ngood ideas of the contents to those\n0who have followed the speeches of\nChamp Clark and other leaders\nThe issues as laid out are as fol\nlowsThe\nThe tariff and the cost of living\nPrices of commodities and the in\ncreased cost of of living\nRepublican extravagance\nCannon arid Cannonism\nPublicity of campaign contribu\ntions\nPresident Taft and his administra\ntion\nThe merchants marine\nCorporations and labor\nr No date has been set as yet for\nthe opening of the headquarters for\nthe Democratic Congressional Cam\npaign Committee\nCommitteeFor\nFor Sale\n600 YARDS DIRT to be excavated\nfrom Imperial Tobacco Co Plant\nApply at once if interested Short\nhaul desired\nMEACHAM CONTRACTING CO\nIncorporated\nLEADER SOLD\nRichard Forbes the Purchas\nDailyI\nIPrinceton\nPrinceton Ky Aug 21The\nPrinceton Leader for the past sev\neral years owned and operated by\nCatlett Bros has been purchased\nby Richard D Forbes of Quarry\nville Pa The new owner will take\ncharge of the paper September 1\nand will continue to conduct it as a\ntwice a week Democratic paper It\nis understood that Mr Forbes con\ntemplates turning the paper into a\ndaily within a few months He had\nbeen negotiating for the purchase of\nthe paper for several weeks and up\non his arrival in Princeton several\ndays ago was impressed with\nthe plant and the opportunity\npresented in Princeton for a hust\nling daily paperand the negotiations\nwere immediately closed The for\nmer owners of the Leader were\nState Senator J R Catlett and\nGeorge F Catlett The later will\nremain with the paper under terms\nagreed upon between him and Mr\nForbes\n50000\nTo loan on firstclass real estate se\nourity The TS KNIGHT CO\nAUTO ACCIDENTS\nOne Days Record of Motor\nMishaps\n1\nR B Dengman of Sapulpa OklaI\nand a party of friends had a narrow I\nescape from death Friday when re\nturning In nn automobile from the\nFrankfort reunlofy diNEIks The\nmachine skldde9er A high emt\n\nI i\nI\nI I\nbankment near Lexington and pin\nned two men under the car None\nwere seriously injured\nE T Hosenheimer son of a mil\nlionaire manufacture was taken into\ncustody by the New York police ta\ntell what he might know concernjng\nthe death of Miss Grace Hough who\nwas hurled from a carriage by aa\nautomobile going at the rate of fifty\nmiles and hour\nFive children were struck by on\nautomobile at the San Antonio Tex\nfair grounds One of the children\nwere probably fatally injured atf J\nthe others were seriously hurt The\ndriver lost control of his machine\nwas also seriously injured\nFIDELITY TRUST CO\ni Votes To Increase Capital\nStock\nILouivllle\nLouisville Ky Aug 22Stock i\nholders of the Fidelity Trust Com\npany at a meeting this afternoon\nunanimously voted to increase the i\ncapital stock of the company from\nSl000000 to 2000000 The net\nshortage of August Ropke former\nassistant secretary of the company\nwas announced 1200000 his groas\nshortage having been reduced by se\ncurities and property turned over to\nthe bank Ropke is still in jail await\ning trial in November\nTheres always something missing\nwithout I W Harper whiskey Its\nso old and so extensively used every\nwhere that we should find it hard to\nI get along without it Sold by W\nR Long Hopkinsville Ky\nWith Grains of SaltP\nStrikingly similar claims of VIC\ntory were made by both Govern\nment and revolutionary forces fol\nlowing a battle which occurred on\nthe Tipitapa River and brought the\narmy of Gen Estrada within fifty\nmiles of the Capital of Nicaragua\nAttempted Kidnaping\nStanford Ky Aug 19Stop\nping their automobile in front of\nthe home of T P Eades a young\nfarmer living five miles from this\ncity an unknown man and woman\nyesterday afternoon demanded that\nMrs Eadea give them her yearold\nson When she refused the woman\nthrew the contents of a bottle of\ncarbolic acid on the young mother\nand the couple then fled in their car\nFull details are not obtainable as yet\nas the place is removed from direct\ncommunication The extent of\nMrs Eads injuries is not known\nNo possible reason can be assigned\nfor the act Mrs Eads before her\nmarriage was Miss Nettie Waller of\nLouisville daughter of a railroad\nengineer\nBanks Object\nFour banking institutions in Lex\nington have formally gone on record\nas opposed to the plan of Secretary\nof State Bruner for an examination\nof State banks by special examuu\nat the expense of the banks then\nselvesChildren\nChildren Cry\nFOR FLETCHERS\nFLETCHERST","height":"28632","width":"19628"}}
